cephsumfs (0.2.2-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * profile_performance.py: fsync test file before reads to flush dirty pages
    to storage before any measurement pass.
  * Drop page cache (via /proc/sys/vm/drop_caches) before each cold-read pass;
    warn clearly if not root and cache drop is unavailable.
  * Report separate cold and warm throughput figures; recommend based on cold
    throughput, which is representative of the XRootD checksumming workload.

 -- Package Maintainer <maintainer@example.com>  Thu, 23 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000

cephsumfs (0.2.1-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Fix run_checksum.sh: call installed cephsumfs binary instead of
    python3 -m cephsumfs (no __main__.py in the package).
  * Remove unused CEPHSUM_PYTHON variable from run_checksum.sh.

 -- Package Maintainer <maintainer@example.com>  Thu, 23 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000

cephsumfs (0.2.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * O_NOATIME fallback for files not owned by the calling process.
  * Short-read detection: log WARNING and abort with EIO on truncated pread.
  * cs_delta now uses monotonic clock to avoid NTP skew.
  * Flag conflict validation: --override/--compute-only/--dry-run rejected
    with --verify/--remove.
  * Logging idempotency fix: NullHandler no longer blocks subsequent real
    handlers.
  * Expanded README: caching behaviour, exit codes, known limitations,
    Ubuntu install, custom algorithm guide.

 -- Package Maintainer <maintainer@example.com>  Wed, 23 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000

